            <li>Image files</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>
<hr>
<section>
    <p>The content stage might be done before, after, or in parallel with the Visual/Interaction Design stage.</p>
    <p>In this stage, the team generates <strong>images</strong> (both pictures and graphics), and <strong>copy</strong> (the words that go on the page).</p>
    <p>Both of these processes are usually guided by <strong>style guides</strong> - established patterns for creating content that will be "on brand" for the client.</p>
    <p>Other consideration include the project goals and requirements, and <strong>optimizing SEO</strong> by choosing words (and, increasingly, images) that will rank highly in search.</p>
</section>
