<section>
    <p>QA testers frequently employ "<strong>headless browsers</strong>" - browsers that run in the background, are programmed to simulate a user, and report back on whether links went to the right URL, buttons performed the correct actions, and images loaded properly.</p>
    <p>They may also use "visual <strong>regression testing</strong>", capturing screenshots of a web page before and after a new feature is added, to see if there were any unexpected consequences.</p>
